The paper deals with image compression and restoration using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of L-infinity fidelity criterion and the focus on preserving small, distinctive structures of the original image suggest that the paper may also fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a new machine learning paradigm for ultra high fidelity image compression, which indicates a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
